  <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
   <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm"/>

   <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Type: version_or_definition
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.version_or_definition">
The <b>version_or_definition</b> type is a formal mechanism to refer either to a <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/> or to a <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>.
</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Entity: Configuration_watched_item
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item">
A <b>Configuration_watched_item</b> is the identification of  a <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/> as a configuration.
<note number="1">
The entity <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/> corresponds to the concept of configuration item defined, in some configuration management standards, as an item subject to configuration management.
</note>
<example>
A <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/> may represent a component of a contracted product, onto which severe safety rules apply and for which configuration management is therefore particularly controlled.</example>
<note number="2">A <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/> may identify a variation of a <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/>, an entire <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/>, or some
portion thereof.
</note>
<note number="3">
A <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/> can be established prior to the existence of a corresponding product.
</note>

</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Entity: Configuration_watched_item  Attribute: id
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item.id">
the identification of the identifier that distinguishes the configuration item.
</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Entity: Configuration_watched_item  Attribute: name
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item.name">
the words by which the configuration item is known.
</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Entity: Configuration_watched_item  Attribute: description
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item.description">
the text which describes the configuration item. The value of the attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Entity: Configuration_watched_item  Attribute: item_context
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item.item_context">
  the <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/> that defines the context in which the configuration item has been defined.
  </ext_description>

    <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Entity: Configuration_watched_item  Attribute: corresponding_design
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
  <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item.corresponding_design">
  the set of instances of the entity data type <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Item_design_association"/> that identify products which provide a solution for the configuration item.
   In this version of the application module, the cardinality of the set shall be not higher than one.

  </ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Entity: Item_design_association
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.Item_design_association">
An <b>Item_design_association</b> is the association of a <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/> with a
<express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> or a <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>.
It specifies that the proposed design is a solution for the <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/>.
<p>If the proposed design is a <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>, the <b>Item_design_association</b> represents the statement that, in the considered definition context, the product version, the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> is a definition of, is considered as a way to implement the <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/>.
</p>
<note number="1"> However, it does not involve that this statement is true in all definition contexts of the product version.
</note>
<p>If the proposed design is a <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/>, the <b>Item_design_association</b> represents the statement that, in all definition contexts, the <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/> is considered as a way to implement the <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/>.
</p>
<note number="2"> However, it does not involve that this statement is true for other versions of the product.
</note>
</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Entity: Item_design_association  Attribute: watched_item
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.Item_design_association.watched_item">
the <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/> for which a product solution is proposed.
</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Entity: Item_design_association  Attribute: proposed_design
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.Item_design_association.proposed_design">
the <express_ref linkend="product_version:arm:Product_version_arm.Product_version"/> or the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> that identifies a product which provides a solution for the <express_ref linkend="configuration_item:arm:Configuration_item_arm.Configuration_watched_item"/>.
</ext_description>

  <!--
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Configuration_item_arm  Entity: Item_design_association  Unique : UR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  -->
    <ext_description linkend="Configuration_item_arm.Item_design_association.ur:UR1">There shall be at most one instance of with the same couple of <b>watched_item</b> and <b>proposed_design</b>.
    <note>However, a product version may be a solution for several configuration items.
    </note>
   </ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
